issue.title: The access token you sent could not be found or is invalid.
issue.body:
Hello Everyone, How are you ?
Now I am working to integrate Next.js with Contentful. so I created new space, and I got space ID and access token ID.

But when I try to get content by using ContentFul API in Next.js.. I am getting `Server Error` like below.
![image](https://github.com/contentful/contentful.js/assets/72724141/041d4e50-0354-43de-8814-1157a01a90a2)

I can't understand why I got this error, and How can I solve it ?

I hope you help me please.
Thanks

comment.body:
Guessing you instantiate your contentful client in a file that also may be used by client side code ? If so then you need to create your contentful client in a file that is only imported by server side so that the process.env can be read. Next will not surface env vars in the client side unless are prepended with `NEXT_PUBLIC_` and also you don't want this env available in the browser etc. 

- https://nextjs.org/docs/pages/building-your-application/configuring/environment-variables
